                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I currently have one computer hooked up to a dsl modem. I want to add a second computer in my living room. The jackass at staples(the closest store within an hour that has computers) tried to sell me a $160.00 router and 2 $80.00 wireless cards. Ive been looking at newegg.com anp price watch and the prices there make baby jesus smile =). Here is my delema I need to know what to look for in a router. I want to play EQ/WoW on both boxes at the same time. Lagg is allready a problem on my current box so I don't want to buy anything that is going to slow things down at all. I have no problem running a cable underneath my house, to the other room or is wireless going to effect my gameplay? Well break time is over i need to get back to work now =\ I will have more questions about the new computer I want to build for eq/WoW for under $1k later.
