                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Unless it's on sale, you need it immediately, or it's relatively inexpensive, NEVER buy computer equipment from something like Staples. You just saw one example in the router price, another are CD's and DVD's which sell for half the price online. 
<br />

<br />
I'd do a google search on the specific one you're looking at. Your DSL provider may even provide tech support for specific brands. I know Verizon supports Linksys routers. Linksys also being one of the largest brands and should be a relatively safe buy. The other largest ones being D-Link, Belkin and Netgear. The truth is that most will perform similarly. 
<br />

<br />
I own a Linksys and from firsthand experience of setting it up, it's really simple and all modern routers should be similar. You'll probably need to refer to the manual or perhaps get help on the explanation of what some of the settings do though since you don't seem to be a techie type. The interface is accessed by any web browser by typing in the address of the router after it's hooked up to your computer (usually 192.168.1.1 or 192.168.2.1). From there you'd log on using the default password or no password. CHANGE THIS IMMEDIATELY. 
<br />

<br />
And last thing about the price, I can get 3 wireless routers and 2 wireless cards for those insane prices. That's why 90% of my purchases that are computer related are done online. 
<br />

<br />
Just make sure you buy from a reputable dealer and try to buy from one with no physical presence in your state to avoid tax. Also watch out for low prices but inflated shipping prices. I hate a lot of etailers that don't show the shipping until after you hit the checkout line.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-style: italic">On the other hand, if your reaction to something I say boils down to "You didn't choose MY side, make MY choice," well, you're not looking for information, you're looking for someone to tell you how smart you are thinking the way you do. --</span> <span style="font-weight: bold">Ed Stroligo</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
