                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I know this isnt answering your question but you really dont need a router with only 2 computers connecting to the internet. In fact routers assign bandwidth very inefficiently so unless you have like 4+ computers connecting through one ip address you should just set up your fastest computer as a gateway for the other computer. Gateways cost you zero dollars and take about 10 minutes to set up. Theres a ton of step by step tutorial in the How To section of <a href="http://www.pcworld.com" target="_blank">www.pcworld.com</a> . The other added benefit of a gateway is that it wont split your total bandwidth between 2 computers like a router does.
<br />

<br />
Just some friendly free advice from a computer guru. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
