                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">ICS in Windows does not do any better sharing bandwidth then most routers.  Almost any Linksys, D-Link, Netgear, etc. router will do what you want using either wireless or wired.
<br />

<br />
By far the highest performance solution would be to use a router with traffic shaping like <a href="http://m0n0.ch/wall/" target="_blank" class="postlink">m0n0wall</a> because you can set up it up to give EQ and other game packets priority.  My network uses DI-804HV routers (I need the VPN features) behind m0n0wall running as a traffic shaping bridge.  No matter what any computers are sending or receiving, EQ always has the lowest possible latency to the internet.
<br />

<br />
Some of the newer Linksys routers have traffic shaping features but I have no experience with them.  I doubt they would work overly well since they have little configurability.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Banished Soul Talc
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">He either fears his fate too much,
