                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Talc wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I do prefer dedicated routers just for the convenience</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This is the crux of it right here, and the reason companies like linksys are making a killing off your average joe consumer. Routers are expensive but simple to use. 
<br />

<br />
Setting up a gateway is potentially confusing and may take a bit (30 secs of google searching) of research to set up. Imo there are very few households that actually require a router. I have 3 computers sharing sharing one highspeed connection. Win XP does a fantastic job with no software required. Id wager I use my bandwidth more efficiently that any router that costs under 100 and its 100% free. YOu can probably have it set up in less time it takes you to get ready to go to the store to buy the router too.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
