                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">To set up a computer as a gateway it has to have two network cards. Taht is cash output (though not much). Also that computer, if it is busy, will interrupt internet access for the other computer (this does happen, I know someone who had this setup and whenever the gateway was either playing an MMO or running a graphics program the second computer would go LD a lot). Buying a router for $40 is not much more cash outlay from buying a second NIC for $15, yes it's more than double but in the long run it's jsut as easy and the gateway computer doesn't have t obe relied upon. It can flake out without disrupting the second computer.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><br>
<br />
<center><img src="http://www.darkhold.com/siggif.jpg" border="0" />
