                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Routers expensive?  Hell...once every couple of weeks I see routers for like $9 after rebate on <a href="http://www.slickdeals.net" target="_blank">www.slickdeals.net</a> or <a href="http://www.techbargains.com" target="_blank">www.techbargains.com</a>.
<br />

<br />
That being said...I prefer Netgear.  I have a Netgear wireless router and it works flawlessly.  I've never had any of the problems that people report about EQ and the Linksys routers (but apparently the Linksys routers are very hackable with all sorts of cool add-ons for traffic shaping and stuff).  I would avoid D-Link.
<br />

<br />
You can set up your main machine as a gateway...but you have to make sure it is on every time you want to access the net from the second computer which can sometimes be a pain in the ass.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
