                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Setting aside that you can get a basic 4 port switch/router for at most $40, when you set up a gateway, you still need to by a hub, unless you put multiple NiCs in the gateway machine. 
<br />

<br />
Security can be an issue...you better have a darn good firewall at least on the gateway machine. 
<br />

<br />
The gateway has to be on to access the internet.
<br />

<br />
Performance? What are we talking here? I can hook one of my computers straight to my cable modem, hit a speed test site like DSL Reports, and get basically the same throughput than when I go through my router.
<br />

<br />
Setting up a gateway, although not that difficult, is not real intuitive. Setting up a router is plug and play..even a caveman can do it ("Not cool, man. Not cool...","oh...that was real condescending..." - Geico...sorry, that commercial is too funny).
<br />

<br />
I'll stick with my routers <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-style: italic">That is all I have to say about that! - Forest Gump</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
