                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Candiarie wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Out of curiousity, does using bittorrent (I use azureus)through a router **** up your speed? I've always used it through a router, but when I have it running every computer linked to it (3) is drastically affected.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
That problem is caused by a lack of traffic shaping at the bottleneck in your internet connection which is normally your DSL, cable, or modem link.  If the router (or computer) which is acting as your gateway supports traffic shaping, then it is possible to completely saturate your link in both directions with a minimal effect on latency.  I regularly run multiple bit torrent sessions, nntp, and various servers with no effect on my EQ sessions at all.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Banished Soul Talc
<br />

<br />
