                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I should add that some of the newer Linksys routers support some kind of traffic shaping but not having used them, I do not know how well they work.  The Linksys routers with 3rd party firmware support also have some kind of traffic shaping.
<br />

<br />
I use m0n0wall myself which is basically FreeBSD with a PHP front end.  It is by far the highest performance solution listed in this thread although quite a bit more techinical.  I would still consider it easy to use and having used it as a router, firewall, and traffic shaper, I will never go back.  For it you just need a spare PC with 2 or 3 network ports that is supported by FreeBSD.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Banished Soul Talc
