                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Vizier wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">With the set up he described (2 computers) you wouldnt need a hub, just an extra $10 Ethernet card, if he didnt already have one.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
A hub runs about $12-15...not sure what the point is. If you are going to connect more than two computers, you are going to want a hub anyway. Speaking of connecting multiple computers...why did you say a gateway is better for 4 or less computers? Why does a router become better for more than 4? Or, why is a gateway better for 4 or less computers?
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Anyhow, nothing on this thread has convinced me that routers are better than a gateway. They are just easier and appeal to lazy / non-tech people. More than anything I think the point i was trying to make was that there are better/faster/cheaper ways to connect computers to the internet than using the lazy mans solution we call a router.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
If you prefer gateways, more power to you. But, I can't let the 'lazy' part go.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline"> Routers offer:</span>
<br />

<br />
- practically zero setup time. Out of the box to online in less than 1 minute (providing there is already a NiC installed)
<br />
- natural firewall
<br />
- only the machine that is going to access the computer needs to be on
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Gateway offers:</span>
<br />

<br />
-slightly better throughput
<br />
-slightly less expensive
<br />

<br />
Judging by that list, I would call choosing a router over a gateway a 'smart' choice, or, at the very least, a flip of the coin choice (personal preference). You don't get away with calling me lazy...sorry <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-style: italic">That is all I have to say about that! - Forest Gump</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
	<tr>
